course_metadata.title: Thermal performance of well insulated building envelopes

content_chunks.content: This course provides an in-depth understanding of heat and moisture transfer processes in modern, highly insulated building envelopes. Students will learn to analyze and design constructions that ensure optimal thermal comfort, energy efficiency, and durability. Topics include heat transfer mechanisms, boundary conditions, thermal bridges, and the performance of thermally inhomogeneous structures such as wooden frame walls. The course also introduces methods for evaluating hygrothermal behaviour, including interstitial condensation risks and moisture transport within building assemblies. Practical sessions involve modelling and simulation tools.

Technology for advanced building envelope analysis and thermal bridge optimization - this course delivers comprehensive expertise in heat transfer mechanisms and moisture transfer processes for modern building envelope analysis applications. Students will master thermal bridge calculation techniques, boundary conditions analysis, and wooden frame construction evaluation for optimal thermal performance optimization. The curriculum focuses on practical air tightness testing methods, blower door testing procedures, and infrared thermography applications for U-value monitoring and interstitial condensation detection. Participants will gain hands-on experience with Glazer calculation methods, dynamic heat-moisture transfer modeling, and building renovation challenges assessment. The program emphasizes building envelope testing protocols, thermal performance optimization strategies, and building envelope analysis using advanced simulation tools for comprehensive building physics solutions.
